-- Bombardier Gets $446 Million Order From India's SpiceJet for 15 Q400s
-- B y   S t e f a n i e   B a t c h o - L i n o
-- 2010-12-09T14:05:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-09/bombardier-gets-446-million-order-from-india-s-spicejet-for-15-q400s.html
Bombardier Inc. said SpiceJet of
Gurgaon, India, placed a firm order for 15 Q400 NextGen
turboprop airliners and has taken options on an additional 15
airliners. The value of the order is about $446 million and
could increase to $915 million if all 15 options are placed,
Bombardier said in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stefanie Batcho-Lino at 
 sbatcholino1@bloomberg.net  